Elia System Operator NV (ELI) , the
operator of electricity grids in  Belgium  and eastern Germany,
plans to invest 3 billion euros ($3.7 billion) over the next 10
years to enhance its grid and develop an off-shore wind farm,
 Belgian magazine Trends  reported.  The company is seeking to improve its grid connections with
France, the Netherlands, Germany and the U.K., Trends reported,
citing an interview with Jacques Vandermeiren and Daniel
Dobbeni, the companyâ€™s incoming and outgoing chief executive
